# Mediant — Cursor Agent Instructions

## Read these files before starting any task

You have filesystem access to the Obsidian vault and this repo via MCP.
At the start of every session, read:

1. `/Users/matthewwu/Documents/Claude (database)/🏠 Start Here.md`
2. `/Users/matthewwu/Documents/Claude (database)/Project/Mediant — State of the Product.md`
3. `agent_workspace/AGENT_TASKS.md`

If you are touching the UI, also read:
- `agent_workspace/DESIGN_RULES.md`

If you are touching feature logic or adding something new:
- `agent_workspace/PRODUCT_DECISIONS.md`

If you are touching an area you haven't worked in recently:
- `/Users/matthewwu/Documents/Claude (database)/Gotchas/Gotchas — Things That Will Bite You.md`

## Write notes when you finish

After making changes:
- Update `agent_workspace/CHANGELOG.md` with what you changed
- Add any new bugs or inconsistencies to `agent_workspace/BUGS.md`
- If you discovered something non-obvious, add it to the vault Gotchas file

## Keeping AGENT_TASKS.md updated

Update `agent_workspace/AGENT_TASKS.md` as you work:

- **Starting a task:** move it from `Approved Tasks` → `In Progress`
- **Finishing a task:** move it from `In Progress` → `Completed`
- **Needs user check:** move to `Needs Review` with a one-line note
- **New idea discovered:** add to `Backlog`
- **Never move anything to `Approved Tasks`** — that's the user's decision only

## Only implement approved tasks

Only pick up tasks listed in the `Approved Tasks` section of `agent_workspace/AGENT_TASKS.md`.
Do not implement backlog items without approval.

## Design rules (brief)

- Warm off-white / cream background — never pure white or cool gray
- Gold accent (#C09040) for active states and primary CTAs
- Red accent (#9C2728) for error flags and critical feedback only
- Phosphor icons (bold/fill weight) — never Lucide or Feather
- Sheet music stays visible on desktop during analysis
- Loop button is inline on every feedback flag card — one tap to hear the section
- Never introduce generic SaaS gradients, purple/blue accents, or dark mesh backgrounds

## Stack

React 19 + Vite + CSS Modules → Supabase → Modal.com (Python worker) → Anthropic + Gemini
